    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\begin{aligned}P&amp;=\lim _{T\to \infty }{\frac {1}{T}}\int _{-\infty }^{\infty }\left[x_{T}(t)+y_{T}(t)\right]^{*}\left[x_{T}(t)+y_{T}(t)\right]dt\\&amp;=\lim _{T\to \infty }{\frac {1}{T}}\int _{-\infty }^{\infty }|x_{T}(t)|^{2}+x_{T}^{*}(t)y_{T}(t)+y_{T}^{*}(t)x_{T}(t)+|y_{T}(t)|^{2}dt\\\end{aligned}}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></div><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/0714e881bda14334fc847bdb3a20dc25c7d77b3d" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-display mw-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -5.505ex; width:65.027ex; height:12.176ex;" alt="{\displaystyle {\begin{aligned}P&amp;=\lim _{T\to \infty }{\frac {1}{T}}\int _{-\infty }^{\infty }\left[x_{T}(t)+y_{T}(t)\right]^{*}\left[x_{T}(t)+y_{T}(t)\right]dt\\&amp;=\lim _{T\to \infty }{\frac {1}{T}}\int _{-\infty }^{\infty }|x_{T}(t)|^{2}+x_{T}^{*}(t)y_{T}(t)+y_{T}^{*}(t)x_{T}(t)+|y_{T}(t)|^{2}dt\\\end{aligned}}}"></div>
</p><p>Using the same notation and methods as used for the power spectral density derivation, we exploit Parseval's theorem and obtain
